column161: It's tough to say who's all 'warm' and 'competent' because there were a few of those races I couldn't place to people I know.
Thanks for the opportunity to participate and good luck with your research!
Thank you for using MTurk and giving me this opportunity
I find it very hard to make judgments about people with so little information
Many thanks!  By the way, I'm not crazy about lawyers in general...haha!
Thank you for letting me participated in the survey.
Thank you and have a nice day!
I hate judging based on first impressions alone but I tried my best!

I tend to make opinions of people based on vibrations, not race or occupations. The gut feeling I have don't apply here as I feel I am forced to judge people racially on things have no clue about. I hope it can help your research but that's not how I think people make judgments in real life.
Thank you for the chance to participate! I didn't really think much about the race/ethnicity of the people---the occupation influenced my impressions more.
I think I forgot to answer the last question?
That was harder than I expected!
Everything was very straightforward. No problems here.

That's really hard to base people off of their jobs and rating them.  I should have put I was confident in my answer 50% of the time for all of them because I don't know the person and I'm probably wrong.
You should have made the "warm" and "competent" much, much, bigger...i dont think i messed any up but it was easy to miss.
I can't tell how a person will be without meeting them.
If it seemed my answers were somewhat similar is because I tend to view people of all groups the same way. Thank you.
Just FYI, I am Greek myself, which may have skewed my impressions!  Thank you for the survey!
